  "prompt": "Where can I get best quality Build In Wardrobes in Guildford?",
  "response": "Finding the \"best quality\" is subjective and depends on your budget, style preferences, and specific needs. However, here's a breakdown of places in and around Guildford that offer built-in wardrobes, along with factors to consider when making your choice:\n\n**Options to Consider:**\n\n*   **Dedicated Wardrobe Companies:**\n    *   **Hammonds:** A well-known national company with showrooms in larger towns around Guildford. They offer a wide range of styles and finishes.  Hammonds typically focuses on high-quality, more premium options.\n\n    *   **Sharps:** Another national brand with a solid reputation. Similar to Hammonds in terms of range and quality.\n\n    *   **Neville Johnson:** Known for high-end bespoke fitted furniture, including wardrobes. They often focus on more unique and elaborate designs.\n\n    *   **Strachan:** Specialises in fitted furniture, including wardrobes, offering a bespoke service.\n\n    *   **Space-pod:** A Surrey-based company offering fitted furniture, including wardrobes. They offer a bespoke service.\n\n*   **Local Carpentry and Joinery Businesses:**\n\n    *   **Pros:** Can offer a truly bespoke service, tailoring the wardrobe exactly to your needs and the dimensions of your space. Often more flexible with design and materials. You can directly communicate your vision and potentially get a better price compared to larger national companies.\n\n    *   **Cons:** Requires careful research to find a reputable and skilled carpenter. You'll need to be more involved in the design process.\n\n    *   **Finding them:** Search online for \"carpenter Guildford,\" \"joiner Guildford,\" \"bespoke wardrobes Guildford,\" or \"fitted wardrobes Guildford.\"  Check online directories, ask for recommendations from friends and neighbours, and look at local Facebook groups.\n\n*   **Kitchen and Bedroom Design Companies:**\n    *   Many kitchen companies also offer fitted bedroom furniture, including wardrobes. If you're already working with a kitchen designer, it's worth checking their wardrobe options.\n    *   Often offers a cohesive design throughout your home.\n\n*   **DIY/Flat-Pack Options with Professional Installation:**\n    *   **IKEA PAX:** IKEA offers a very customizable wardrobe system with different door styles, interior fittings, and sizes. While you assemble yourself, you can hire professional installers to ensure it's done correctly.  A budget-friendly option.\n\n    *   **Howdens:** Trade supplier, usually you would use a builder or fitter to design and install but a trade account is not always required and you can often get a good service this way.\n\n**Factors to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Budget:**  Essential to determine your price range before you start looking. Bespoke options will be more expensive than modular systems.\n*   **Style:**  Consider the overall style of your bedroom and choose a wardrobe that complements it.  Think about the door style (sliding, hinged, mirrored), finish (wood, painted, laminate), and hardware.\n*   **Space:**  Accurately measure your space, paying attention to ceiling height, wall angles, and any obstructions (e.g., radiators, electrical sockets).\n*   **Storage Needs:**  Think about what you need to store in the wardrobe \u2013 clothes (hanging, folded), shoes, accessories, etc. Plan the interior layout accordingly (shelves, drawers, hanging rails, shoe racks).\n*   **Materials and Construction:**  Look for durable materials (e.g., solid wood, quality plywood or MDF) and sturdy construction. Ask about warranties and guarantees.\n*   **Reputation and Reviews:**  Check online reviews and testimonials for any company you're considering.  Ask for references from previous customers.\n*   **Installation:**  Ensure the company offers professional installation services, or that you have a reliable installer lined up.\n\n**Steps to Take:**\n\n1.  **Define Your Needs:** Determine your budget, style preferences, and storage requirements.\n2.  **Research:**  Search online, read reviews, and ask for recommendations.\n3.  **Get Quotes:**  Contact several companies for quotes, providing them with accurate measurements and your specific requirements.\n4.  **Visit Showrooms (if possible):** Seeing the quality of materials and workmanship in person is invaluable.\n5.  **Ask Questions:**  Don't hesitate to ask questions about materials, construction, warranties, and installation.\n6.  **Check References:**  If possible, contact previous customers to get their feedback on the company's work.\n7.  **Read the Contract Carefully:**  Before signing any contract, make sure you understand all the terms and conditions, including payment schedules, delivery times, and cancellation policies.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nThe \"best\" built-in wardrobe depends on *your* definition of quality and your specific needs.  Start with research, get multiple quotes, and don't be afraid to ask questions. Good luck!\n",
